Sphinx Documentation
--------------------

Note: Sphinx actually runs and imports python code, so broken code,
      or code not in conf.py sys.path, cannot be documented!

-  Get Sphinx 
    Easier way:
    [easy_install sphinx]
    
    Harder way:
    [http://sphinx.pocoo.org/]    
    [python setup.py build/install]
    
-  Optional, do this step if you activate numpy extension in conf.py 
    Install numpydoc 
    Easier way:
    [easy_install numpydoc]
    
    Harder way:
    [http://pypi.python.org/pypi/numpydoc] 
    
   
Choose method 1 or 2. Method 1 is easier!

Method 1:
- From the modaldecomp directory, run 
      sphinx-build doc doc/_build
      
- Open doc/_build/index.html to view the documentation


Method 2:
-  In Makefile point to your own copy of sphinx-build, e.g.
    [SPHINXBUILD   = /Users/yourname/CODES/Sphinx-1.0.6/sphinx-build.py]

-  From within doc/ directory 
    >> touch *.rst
    >> make html  [or make latex]

-  Navigate to doc/_build/html and open index.html to view and browse the documentation




